
'''* Book: The Mermaid and the Minotaur: Sexual Arrangements and the Human Malaiseby Dorothy Dinnerstein.'''

URL = http://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/product/0060905875

=Discussion=

Anna Harris:

"It was written in 1977, but it is still the best fundamental analysis of men/women differences I know of. It gets you to understand the situation, as opposed to deploring some of its effects. And it makes the link to the social and civilizational consequences.

Since those years I have offered it to many people. Only one friend, a woman, has really read it and valued it as I do.
In the vast literature on that subject it is only rarely mentioned, and even then only about side issues, not the core message.

I think the reason of that lack of interest is that the core message is not easy to stomach for most people, it does not play the blame game. It invites us to look at fundamental parts of our inner psychological structure, and instead of just claiming or blaming them as given by 'nature', understand how they 'naturally' come about, including their pathological aspects, individual and social, and try to consciously deal with them. If you care about the future of humanity, read it."
(networked labour mailing list, January 2014)

